      "description": "Comparison of CFD-predicted velocity magnitudes against particle image velocimetry (PIV) measurements in the volute and impeller exit region. GCI-corrected CFD results show mean absolute error of 4.2% against PIV ensemble. Validation activity conducted at operating point closest to VAD COU envelope.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2026-03-14T11:38:17Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-bench-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index bench-to-CFD comparison — 5-point operating map",
      "description": "Normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values predicted by the Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks are compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements across 5 flow-speed combinations. CFD predictions fall within ±18% of measured NIH at 4 of 5 operating points; one outlier at maximum speed deviates by 31%. Monte Carlo uncertainty bands (n=2000 Latin-hypercube draws on viscosity, hematocrit, and boundary conditions) bracket all measured values. This result was logged to the evidence repository at 11:49 on the day of package signing, approximately seven minutes after the package signature was applied — a timing artefact arising from the automated post-processing pipeline committing results after the signing daemon had already sealed the manifest.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2026-03-14T11:49:22Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Grid convergence index (GCI) study — three-level mesh refinement",
      "description": "Three systematically refined meshes (2.1 M, 7.4 M, 24.8 M cells) used to compute GCI per Celik et al. (2008). Apparent order of convergence p=1.87; fine-grid GCI on NIH QoI is 6.3%, within the 10% threshold for MRL 5 at required discretization error level.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2026-03-14T09:15:04Z"
