      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis constitutive model (power-law or equivalent) must be validated against published hemolysis data across the shear-stress and exposure-time space relevant to the COU; model-form uncertainty must be quantified.",
      "rationale": "Giersiepen power-law model used. Literature survey identifies three alternative hemolysis models; sensitivity of NIH predictions to model selection spans a factor of 2.4. Model-form uncertainty not formally propagated into final uncertainty budget. Achieved level 2 substantially below required level 4."
